LCgt1YB4BvSDGdXK21b0Bela.text: This library simulates [Engduino board] (http://www.engduino.org/). You play with it as it is, but you can also export simple TouchDevelop scripts to run on the actual board.

ObP2KOVj9sepKBokqUyGzTAe.text: * Write a script which references this library (or use one of the existing ones)

AyP48ioXqABDrRgYyNuf6e9a.text: * Go to `[script properties]` (click on the name of the script, next to the `[publish]` button, in code editor)

qk72rbwKDxtkebvmU4232rSf.text: When exporting to the board most TouchDevelop APIs will not work. Only use the ones defined in this library, or the ones which are mentioned here.

w2eSNQch7zR8rV9gPqYQqfZo.text: You can use `senses->acceleration quick` and friends. These will work on the board. Additionally, you can use `code->button pressed` and `code->button was pressed`.
